<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="85" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Acalypha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acalypha lamiana" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lamiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Acalypha lamiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was treated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Leandri, J" journalOrPublisher="Notululae Systematicae" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" pagination="252 - 290" refId="B31" refString="Leandri, J, 1942. Acalypha. Contribution a l'etude des Euphorbiacees de Madagascar (VI). Notululae Systematicae 10: 252 - 290" title="Acalypha. Contribution a l'etude des Euphorbiacees de Madagascar (VI)." volume="10" year="1942">Leandri (1942)</bibRefCitation>
as a form of 
<taxonomicName family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. reticulata var. urophylla" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="variety" species="reticulata" variety="urophylla">A. reticulata var. urophylla</taxonomicName>
(Boivin ex Baill.) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Müll">Muell</normalizedToken>
.Arg. (treated here as 
<taxonomicName family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. urophylla" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="species" species="urophylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">A. urophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). After studying the numerous type collections, it seems clear to us that 
<taxonomicName family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. lamiana" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="species" species="lamiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">A. lamiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be considered as a distinct species. 
<taxonomicName family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. lamiana" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="species" species="lamiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">A. lamiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. urophylla" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="species" species="urophylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">A. urophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly by the leaves that are rounded at the base and reddish at the margins and its subentire, eglandular female bracts vs. leaves that are usually acute at the base and not reddish at the margins and dentate female bracts with small sessile glands at margins, in 
<taxonomicName family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. urophylla" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="species" species="urophylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">A. urophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
